🌸 Iris Flower Classification Web App

This project is a Flask web application that predicts the type of Iris flower (Setosa, Versicolor, Virginica) based on user inputs.
It uses a trained Machine Learning model (saved with joblib) and also visualizes prediction probabilities with bar and pie charts.

🚀 Features

📝 Simple input form for sepal & petal dimensions

🤖 Predicts Iris flower species using a trained model

📊 Generates Bar Chart & Pie Chart of prediction probabilities

🌐 Built with Flask, scikit-learn, and Matplotlib

🛠️ Tech Stack

Python (Flask, NumPy, Matplotlib, scikit-learn, joblib)

HTML + CSS (Frontend)

Flask Templates (Jinja2)

📂 Project Structure
├── app.py                 # Main Flask app
├── model.pkl              # Trained ML model
├── templates/
│   ├── index.html         # Input page
│   ├── result.html        # Prediction result page
├── static/
│   ├── prediction_bar.png # Auto-generated bar chart
│   ├── prediction_pie.png # Auto-generated pie chart
└── README.md              # Documentation

⚙️ Installation & Setup

Clone the repo:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/iris-flask-app.git
cd iris-flask-app


Install dependencies:

pip install flask joblib scikit-learn matplotlib numpy


Run the Flask app:

python app.py


Open in browser:

http://127.0.0.1:5000/

📊 Example Output

Prediction result with probability distribution

Auto-generated Bar Chart and Pie Chart for better visualization

